address: 103 Streatham Hill, London SW2 4UE, United Kingdom
name: Rathna Ali
text:
Went with two teens to try out the mini golf on a Sunday afternoon. Honestly - terrible! I'll start with arrival and then explain the 7 hole course.

On arrival, met with a really unenthusiastic unsmiling lady behind the bar who seemed to be more interested in her conversation with her pal sat drinking at the bar than in engaging with what few customers they had. We weren't shown to the course - we were given balls piece of paper and pencil and left to get on with it. I ordered 2 sprites which was £7.

Hole 2 had broken glass in one of the holes that you were supposed to putt through. Luckily for us a couple before us had warned us in time - I dread to think what would have happened if they had not had the forethought! The staff certainly didn't seem to care.

The course itself was abysmal, really poorly laid out and not at all fun or imaginative - we invented our own "rules" to make it somewhat fun. Sometimes the end hole was right next to where you started from - and only one obstacle which wasn't actually in line - but you could infer you were supposed to follow that line. Hole 6 I believe we found a discarded false nail on the course - and Hole 7 huge letdown - no real challenge fun at the end.

Overall, this could have been a lot better. We were there at 5pm on a Sunday - sure after a Saturday night, but you'd think the staff would have cared to have cleaned up by then. Tables and floors felt sticky and there were mop buckets of stank water left around. My son slipped on a bit and touched a gross looking wet floor.

There were a couple of old arcade machines we had a couple of gos at - but the most fun was the air hockey table which was not free and cost £1.50 a go - my teens played 2 games.

So overall spend - mini golf - £10 adult + £16 2 kids + £3 air hockey + £7 2 sprites = £36.

I would not recommend and would not ever go back - much better to travel in to Puttshack.

Honestly only 2 stars because we did spend about 60mins and there was an Air hockey machine

text:
The bad:
Mini golf - just don’t bother. As other reviews have mentioned it’s cramped and poorly built. The layout of the holes just doesn’t make sense at all, it’s actually laughable. It’s a shame because there’s so much potential with the amount of space the venue has and features such as the old bank vault.

The name ‘putt putt’ suggests the focus should be on the mini golf and that’s just got lost.

The good:
I liked the atmosphere, the cocktails were good, and while we didn’t play the board games, darts, pool etc. they’re a nice touch

text:
I was there that night, my cousin's birthday. I went to the bar to order a drink and there was a line. I was surprised, I looked closely and there was NOBODY in the bar. I waited 10 minutes when the bartender came out COMPLETELY HIGH and started taking orders. when it was my turn, the  YELLED that he wasn't going to make any cocktails because he was BUSY.
I spoke with my cousin, she went to the bar and he apologized and stated that he was busy and asked me for a free drink, I didn't accept! I left immediately and as I left he said: there was no way I could guess where you were. In this case, did I need to say that I was participating in the birthday to be served correctly??? If he had told me that the drink in question wasn't available, ok. But shouting that you won't do it because you're busy? no conditions.

text:
First and foremost, Putt Putt embodies the word "fun" unlike any other place I've been to in London.

As other reviews have said, if you're looking strictly for the best mini golf in town, there are better options.

But the chaotic mix of table tennis, arcades, pool and most importantly the karaoke sections turn this into one big rich kid's house party

It's also understated that they offer a lot of this stuff for free, super rare these days - so bring ten of your mates and forget about the world for a while!

Cant talk about the staff, as apart from paying £29 for two people to play golf with a soft drink and a wine. We didnt see or speak to any one esle.
Venue:
Has the look of a youth centre but without the atmosphere or people. Everything is quashed into every available space. There is everything your kids to play, but like every Youth centre its all falling apart or badly put together.
Mini Golf:
The first three hole occupy the same space as the dart board. For safety both shouldn't be played at the same time. As you can see from the pictures it looks like they went to B&Q bought the cheapest fake grass, some pipes and off cut timber. No time has been taken to consider game play. The hole dont tell you how to take the shot (like every other miningolf i have ever played). Although being so small its not hard to work it out. They have used the wrong pile, and the grass  length impedes the balls travel. Just dont hit it to hard or it may injure someone. If you manage to get the ball to move across the grass the holes are so badly put together that we had to help it through the "tunnel". We had to lift the grass and put it theough the pipe in order to get our ball out. The ring 4 holes, yes only 7 holes for your money, were downstairs. The double loop in the vault again lined with grass slow the ball down enough the make it impossible to complete the loops. Then there are two very steep inclines, the first has karaoke seating beside it. Again be careful seating here. Thankfully it was empty when we was there. The second was soo tight that you could barely to in.
I feel it has taken me longer to write this review, then it did to play the mini golf.
Conclusion i wont be bringing the group here,  Glad I did a recki first, Streatham has such a great night life, shame Putt Putt cant be apart of that.

text:

I felt so bad for this very lovely woman, I offered her a job at my firm knowing she is terrified of her boss. Please do not come to this place.

responseFromOwnerText:
Sorry but our karaoke is not Privat!!
And your woucher was expired!!!
And  I gave you a slot for Friday evening,,
I gave to stay more of 2 hours!
So anyway thanks for your coming...!!!
text:
This is one of the worst places I’ve ever been to. I booked in for Karaoke via a Wowcher, when we got there, the karaoke room was already filled with a private party. Someone was having a full blown birthday party, full food spread table, banners, balloons the works! The manager came down and told them we would be using the room too and we could play one song each for the night, except they weren’t there for singing. So we sang one song and they would choose one song to dance to and that’s how it played out.
They were very nice people and very patient with our singing interrupting their private party. He said they had changed the way they run the place, there are no private rooms anymore and this is how they run now.

The actual Karaoke itself was us choosing a song from YouTube and singing along and they didn’t even have premium so we had to watch an advert between each song. I think this annoyed me the most, if you are going to advertise as a venue for karaoke, even one who just uses YouTube (which in itself is ridiculous) pay for premium!

It was shockingly bad, we could’ve done this at home, at least we wouldn’t have any adverts and wouldn’t be interrupting someone else’s birthday party!

As we were singing and probably annoying the other group, people would be playing mini golf right in the way of the screen. One of the mini golf holes was the stairs…

Because it wasn’t a private room and we were sharing the YouTube with another group, a guy walked in, who was really drunk and started singing weird songs and talking about sex and swearing. It took a long time to work out he was a random and not with the other group, they thought he was with us. We had to remove him ourselves.

It was the most ridiculous night out I’ve ever had. It was so bad that it was almost funny. Except it was a suprise birthday party for my husband so I’m pretty annoyed but he found it funny.

I will say this, I bought my Wowcher in August and it expired on 17th September and they let me come on 8th October which was a lovely thing to do, so that’s why they are getting 2 stars, otherwise it would be one.

Avoid this place.

address: 103 Streatham Hill, London SW2 4UE, United Kingdom
name: Daniel González
text: Not a great experience. As fancy as the place looks from the outside, this business is not up to expectations: the website does not offer any reminiscence of the actual place and it is misleading -not a single picture is the actual place and they claim to be the "biggest indoor crazy golf in London" while in reality is the biggest disappointment in Streatham. While booking the gold course is quite easy online, the confirmation email does not even say date or time -simply a 10am to 11.30pm booking, when they do not really open that early. You will not know if you did the booking correctly. The phone provided does not work and they do not reply to emails. I had to actually go and double check that the reservation was okay for the day and the person at front simply said "sure, come in any time". They did not check the reservation when returning -assuming they remember me from when I went to check my booking was correct?-, and simply handle a couple of golf balls and the points sheet. There are two levels: 7 holes upstairs -only worth the first 3, being number 3 a really hard one- and another 7 wholes downstairs. Most of the wholes need to be redesign as they do not have any hints nor explanation and I had a feeling that the design is not calculated to be fun but rather challenging by the shake of it. They basically do not comply with physics rules. Downstairs remains more of a Saw film than a mini golf course. They have utilised the warehouse area to make it look a "money heist" course, but it is an actual "warehouse" course, with several doors locked and unsigned, confusing holes and arrows, and a "crafty" design with materials that are closer to an "art attack" project than a professional business. Neil Buchannan's paper mâché was for sure stronger than some of the materials in Putt Putt. Staplers are all over the place and there are risks of accidents, specially downstairs with the poor light and stairs around. It could be one of those experiences that it is so bad that it is fun, but not for £20 per person (or £10 upstairs/£15 upstairs). Not worth it. The bar area is as wide as an airplane corridor, aside two tables areas -one next to a ping pong table and one right in the middle of a hole downstairs. I cannot talk about the drinks or food as we left as soon as possible -around 20 minutes course for £20 if you actually try to ace in every hole (good luck). No Karaoke room on site. No cloakroom either so be ready to carry your belongings around the narrow course. Upsetting.

text:
I've not reviewed before, welcome to my first one, usually I don't do reviews but this had to be done.
The worst crazy golf putting since golf begun. DO NOT COME HERE, is zero stars not an option?

Don't make the same mistake.

Uninspiring, rude, poor design, no cloak room... the list goes on, but I'm done.
We turned up, placed bets, but in the end nobody won.
Used balls abandoned on the final hole say, "you're not the only one". Golf elsewhere. Anywhere else.
Just take broomstick and balls to Streatham Common.

Now I'm waiting for my mate who arranged the night to refund me.
Plenty of warning on these google reviews yet he still booked. Rookie.

address: 103 Streatham Hill, London SW2 4UE, United Kingdom
name: Oliver Poulter
text:
I'm finding it hard to put into words just how awful this experience was, but in the spirit of honesty I'll do my best.

From the outside this place looks legit, Crayola green exterior with a flashing neon sign (classy). But unfortunately when crossing the threshold that thin veneer of hope dissolves and the nightmare begins.

We were greeted by an angry looking man who served us flat beer and demanded we wait until clubs become available to use. (Apparently they didn't have enough clubs). The man continued to be angry and the beer continued to be flat but as mini golf enthusiasts we persevered hoping this would be a small set back in what would otherwise be a fruitful night of family friendly golfing.

I'll cut to the chase here, The golf course itself was bad.. Really really bad.   None of the holes were actually designed in a way that would allow you to  play the course and most of the time it felt as if we were walking through a south London squat as opposed to an entertainment venue.

Whoever designed the course shouldn't design any more mini golf courses and the craftsmanship left little to be desired. Everything felt like it was going to fall apart not to mention all of the protruding nails that were genuine health and safety risks.

After my brother cut his hand on a nail on the 14th (photo attached) we decided to call it a night and console ourselves over a wing roulette platter from the local Nandos. I made the angry man on the bar aware of the nail, he shrugged his shoulders, continued to look angry and poured more flat beer for fresh faced customers entering the warzone.

Not good golfing, won't return and you shouldn't either.
title: Putt Putt & Karaoke Bar

responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Sarah,

We had a special day on the New Year's Day and we announced on our social media that we will be opening from 8 PM. We are sorry that this message didn't get across all customers and I can see per our records that you refund has been processed yesterday

We hope we will see you soon at our venue and the entertainment you and your children will have here will change your review
text:
I booked this for £60 on New Year’s Day via their website. We turned up and it was closed (2 disappointed children). These things happen but I have e-mailed and phoned to get my money back for over a week and no response. Be careful!

Reply to the response -No I have not received a refund. This is not a great method of communicating-can you reply to my e-mails or calls please?

It looks like you think it’s suitable to have a booking system that takes booking for services you can not fulfill?

name: James
text: So bad that it made it entertaining. Holes have been rushed and have been completed on the cheap. You can see where the turf has been stapled in, the course is uneven in places (especially on the slopes and ramps), most holes are utterly pointless. The signs for the hole numbers are unclear. £15 for both courses laughable, especially when you it takes 5 minutes to complete each course. The bar area looks like a student house dining room and not somewhere you'd want to stay for a drink, particularly at those prices. All feels like a bit of a scam

responseFromOwnerText:
Hi Alice,

Many thanks for your constructive feedback, we will take a note on this and will do our best to try and make sure that all of the above will be done as soon as possible
text:
Great concept, execution leaves a lot to be desired. Some of the holes are tricky meaning there's likely to be a queue (hole 3 for example) and from what I can see the karaoke room is yet to be set up. The downstairs holes look like they could be great but I think need a bit of work. The signage will definitely help when it arrives!
I really hope it improves as it opens up properly but can't say I whole heartedly recommend a visit.

text: Not worth it. “Mini” in every sense of the word, the course takes about 5 minutes and has some of the most basic ‘obstacles’ you can imagine. It is far from fun and feels cheap and poorly constructed. Don’t waste your time or money here. Drinks overpriced as well (£8.75 for a single + mixer).

name: Keith Trimmings
responseFromOwnerText: Thank you very much for your review. We were happy to see you at our venue and will be grateful to see you back soon. Merry Christmas
text:
Yes believe it or not a venue with a miniture golf course , I didn't know whether to try for a hole in one or order a pint. Very well designed and decorated to a high standard very upmarket and contempary. Seating is very comfortable and well thought out .
Although the golf course takes up alot of space , and the bar itself is tiny 10 foot ,if that . So I expect when full there may be queues longer than waiting in line for a jab , joke. Well I loved it , what a change and delight , the staff were very welcoming and happy thank god , yes it was a great atmosphere there .I give it my own rating which is very rare of 1 platinum star , well deserved . Go there and see for yourselves , your be surprised,  well it put a smile on my face.
